&lt;p&gt;
	Dan&#39;s Caf&eacute; serves all day breakfasts, a range of freshly made sandwiches, wraps, pannini&#39;s, bagels, salads and soups. Sweet treats include a range of Home baked pastries, cakes, scones and tarts served with Maud&#39;s ice-cream. Tea, Coffee and Cold Drinks available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Dan&rsquo; Stonewall Caf&eacute; open 7 days a week 9am to 6pm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
	The Anchor Bar, known locally as &lsquo;PJ&rsquo;s, is Carlingfords&rsquo; best known and most popular bar. Located in the village centre our traditional bar is extremely popular with both locals and visitors alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Lounge Bar, open at weekends is a tasteful extension by the current owners, Michael and Bernadette Heeney. Fully air conditioned and spacious, the Lounge Bar boasts a big screen television on which all live sport is shown during the day. The Lounge Bar is also Carlingfords&rsquo; main venue every Friday &amp; Saturday night, attracting visitors from far and wide and providing the perfect party atmosphere for young and old alike.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
	We offer good fine simple cooking with a wide range of local seafood in our display cabinet, and our special serlection displayed on our blackboard all from around the bay of Carlingford and across the water to Kilkeel with its abundance of fishing boats, along with local beef and poultry from the local farms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Within just one hour drive from both Dublin and Belfast, situated in the medieval heritage town of Carlingford, along the paved Tholsel street, with past relics such as The Mint (built in 1467) which still stands today. Also The Thosel (or Gate Tower) with its entrance from the north leading into Tholsel Street remains in excellent condition. Here you can discover a charming atmostphere of fine shops all within the surrounding views of Carlingford lough, King John&#39;s Castle and The Mourne Mountain. Close to the heart of the Medieval centre of Carlingford and under the protective shadow of The Tholsel Gate stands Magees Bistro, it offers short menu&#39;s of fresh seasonal food defined as modern. It&#39;s modern style and decor of the dining room with its open kitchen and all our beef is local Irish, cooked on our built in natural charcoal B.B.Q, which allows you to see steak being cooked, and to relax and appreciate its fine cuisine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
	Award winning Deli &amp; Food Hall in the Medieval Village of Carlingford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Food For Thought is an award winning Delicatessen and Food Hall in the heart of Medieval Carlingford, Co Louth. There are over 2,000 speciality food items from Ireland and worldwide, so you have a vast range of foods to choose from.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
	Br&uacute; na B&oacute;inne Visitor Centre interprets the Neolithic monuments of Newgrange, Knowth and Dowth. The extensive exhibition includes a full scale replica of the chamber at Newgrange as well as a full model of one of the smaller tombs at Knowth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All admission to Newgrange and Knowth is through the Visitor Centre, there is no direct access to these monuments. Visitors are brought from the Visitor Centre to the monuments by shuttle bus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;
	Black Bush Golf Club was founded in 1987 and designed by Bobby Browne the resident Professional at Laytown &amp; Bettystown who has served as Secretary of the Irish PGA for many years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;
	Black Bush Golf Club is a magnificent 27-hole complex, giving the golfer a choice of playing three different 18-holes or 9-holes whichever he or she desires. Each course has its own charm and character all within this pleasant Parkland setting. The course matured rapidly and now features tree lined fairways with undulating sand based greens, combine with lengthy holes and the occasional water hazard, add up to a challenging round of golf for the keen players but is also a fair test of golf for the novice. The complex has excellent catering and bar facilities, suitable for conferences and large groups.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
	When you are celebrating and you want to know you look good - look no further than Buttercrane Shopping Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Great Classic Fashion is on show from some of the best fashion stores around for ladies and gents, boys and girls, men and women. Based in Newry, Buttercrane Shopping Centre is one of the largest shopping centres in Northern Ireland.&lt;br /&gt;
