&lt;p&gt;
	Carlingford Adventure Centre recently celebrated 20 successful years in business. From their humble beginnings in, what used to be the old bonded warehouse in the centre of this quaint Medieval Village, this family run business has grown from strength to strength.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Founded by Tom and Mary McArdle in 1990 the family tradition is now carried on by their son, Thomas. The idea was born after a holiday in Achill by Mary and Tom, they planned to open a hostel and take a gamble with the adventure centre as well......&lt;/p&gt;
