&lt;p&gt;
	In a survey conducted by &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.likeplace.ie/zeitgeist/&quot;&gt;LikePlace.ie&lt;/a&gt;, Carlingford in Co Louth was voted, surprisingly, as the top place to live in Ireland. With 6,066 votes cast and counting, the Louth town has an impressive ranking of 4.5 out of 5 points.&lt;/p&gt;
